<diV>
    <h5>Member</h5>
    1. The Library Authority extends membership to persons who reside outside the administrative County of Surrey.<br>
    2. Membership is available to anyone whose residence or place of work is within the administrative County of Surrey or who is undergoing full-time education within the area.<br>
    3. Charges are payable for the borrowing of some audio/visual materials and other items as the Library Authority shall determine.<br>
</diV>
<br>
<div>
    <h5>Registration of members</h5>
    1. A person must register as a member in order to obtain lending facilities and must undertake to observe the Terms and Conditions.<br>
    2. Children who have not reached 16 years of age must register with the consent of their parent or guardian, who are required to be responsible for items borrowed by the child and to pay any charges incurred.<br>
    3. For full membership a person's identity and place of residence, both permanent and temporary, must be established by production of documentary proof, which is acceptable to the Librarian.<br>
</div>
<br>
<div>
    <h5>Library cards</h5>
    1. Full library membership is removed if the card is not used to borrow items for two years.<br>
    2. A member who loses or damages their library card is liable to pay a replacement charge. The Librarian may waive the charge in cases of individual hardship.<br>
    3. The normal loan period for books is 21 days. At the discretion of the Librarian, this period may be reduced for books in demand.<br>
</div>
<br>
<div>
    <h5>Charges</h5>
    1. Some audio/visual items are subject to a hire charge. Additional charges will be payable for each day that an item is kept on loan. Items may be recalled if reserved by another borrower.<br>
    2. Persons unable to use printed material are exempt from the payment of hire charges for audio books.<br>
    3. Members are responsible for paying the replacement value, as assessed by the Librarian, of any item lost or damaged whilst on loan to them.<br>
</div>
